The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 January is 31,625 (3,660.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 January, there were 4,521 new confirmed cases (523.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 January, there were 5,751 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 21% (1,230 fewer cases).
